🟢 Beginner Level
1. What is shadow DOM?
- Shadow DOM is an hidden DOM attached to an element, used for encapsulation

2. Why do we use Shadow DOM?
- To :
    - Avoid CSS conflicts
    - Create reusable components
    - Maintain encapsulation

3. What do you mean by encapsulation?
- It means Internal elements are isolated from outside code. (CSS & JS)

4. What is isolation in Shadow DOM?
- Styles and scripts inside and outside do not affect each other

5. What is a Shadow Host?
- The element to which shadow DOM is attached

6. What is Shadow Root?
- Entry point to access Shadow DOM

7. What is Shadow Tree?
- All elements inside the Shadow DOM

8. Types of Shadow DOM?
- Open
- Closed

9. Difference between Open and Closed Shadow DOM?
- Open -> Accessible
- Closed -> Not accessible

10. How to identify Shadow DOM in browser?
- Look for #shadow-root(open)

🟡 Intermediate Level

11. Can Selenium directly access Shadow DOM?
- NO

12. Why Selenium cannot access Shadow DOM?
- Because it is hidden and encapsulated from normal DOM

13. How do you handle Shadow DOM in Selenium?
- Using:
    - Javascript executor
    - shadow_root (Selenium 4)

14. Write code to access Shadow DOM
host = driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "host-element")
shadow = host.shadow_root
shadow.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "input").send_keys("Hi")

15. What is execute_script used for?
- To run javascript in browser

16. What is arguments[0] in JS?
- It refers to element passed from Selenium

17. Why prefer CSS selectors in Shadow DOM?
- XPATH doesn't work reliably inside shadow DOM

18. Can we use XPath inside Shadow DOM?
-  NOT supported & Mostly not recommended

19. What happens if you skip shadow_root?
- You can not access elements -> test fails

20. Real-time example of Shadow DOM?
- Date picker, video control , UI components

🔴 Advanced Level

21. How do you handle nested Shadow DOM?

host1 = driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "parent-host")
shadow1 = host1.shadow_root

host2 = shadow1.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "child-host")
shadow2 = host2.shadow_root

shadow2.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "input").send_keys("Hi")

22. Can shadow_root handle nested DOM directly?
- NO,Only one level at a time

23. What is the limitation of Selenium with Shadow DOM?
- Cannot access closed Shadow DOM

24. How to handle closed Shadow DOM?
- Not possible in selenium
- Need:
    - Developer support
    - Alternative approach

25. Difference between Shadow DOM and iFrame?
Shadow DOM & iFrame
-------------------
- Hidden DOM , Separate Document
- Same page , different page
- Use show_root , use switch_to_frame()

26. What is the role of JavaScript in Shadow DOM?
- used to extract shadow root 

27. What is encapsulation advantage?
- Prevents UI breaking due to external styles

28. How to debug Shadow DOM issues?
- Use DevTools -> Inspect shadow root

29. What happens if Shadow DOM is dynamic?
- Use Explicit waits (WebDriverWait)

30. Can we automate all Shadow DOM elements?
- Only open shadow DOM

🔥 Tricky / Scenario-Based Questions

31. Your locator is correct but element not found. Why?
- May be inside shadow DOM

32. How do you confirm it's Shadow DOM issue?
- Check for #shadow-root (open)

33. Your script works for one level but fails for nested. Why?
- Not accessing all shadow roots

34. XPath not working, what could be reason?
- Element inside shadow DOM

35. How do you design framework for Shadow DOM?
- Create reusable method 
    def get_shadow_element(driver, host, selector):
    shadow = host.shadow_root
    return shadow.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, selector)

